Just south of the Brandenburg Gate is Berlin‚Äôs Holocaust Memorial, with its two thousand, seven hundred and eleven gray concrete slabs, or stelae.¬†The installation is a living experiment in montage, a¬†Kuleshov effect¬†of the juxtaposition of image and text. In the city of Berlin, on September 24th, our journey towards memory begins with a first major theme: the persecution of the Jews. The emotions and curiosity push us to know the story of a minority that has been crushed. The anguish and sadness helped us to better understand the injustices they suffered. Our images represent the two possibilities these people had: death and hope.
